{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, if a claim can be verified by a specific snippet within an evidence, the remaining segments (including the context of the snippet) will be considered redundant.",
    "The authors employed a 1-layer GGNN to calculate the redundancy scores, considering both self-information and contextual information in the computation process.",
    "Additionally, they conducted semantic structure refinement only on evidences, as claims typically tend to be shorter in length.",
    "Lastly, they stacked the semantic structure refinement layer on top of a semantics encoder, creating a unified module known as evidence semantics miner (ESM).",
    "This module effectively captures long-distance semantic dependencies and reduces redundant information. 4."
  ]
}